summary:
The Security Council,
 Reaffirming previous resolutions on Timor-Leste, 
Commending the people and Government of Timor-Leste for peace and stability, 
Welcoming progress made by UNMISET, 
 Paying tribute to bilateral and multilateral partners, 
Noting Timor-Leste has not yet reached self-sufficiency, 
Welcoming cooperation between Timor-Leste and its neighbours, 
Commending the Serious Crimes Unit, 
 Noting with concern the Unit may not fully respond to the desire for justice, 
 Taking note of the Secretary-General’s reports, 
 Remaining committed to security and stability in Timor-Leste,

1. Extends UNMISET’s mandate for a final 6-month period until 20 May 2005;
2. Maintains UNMISET’s current tasks, configuration and size;
3. Requests UNMISET to focus on implementing its exit strategy;
4. Urges the donor community to continue providing assistance;
5. Urges UN development and humanitarian agencies to plan for a smooth transition;
6. Reaffirms the need to fight against impunity;
7. Requests the Secretary-General to keep the Security Council informed; 
8. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
